      "id": "note_1",
      "text": "IS THE DIFFERENCE REAL? — NZ Yr 11–13\n\nHidden truth: a real difference IS built in — weekend mean (62) is 12 units above weekday (50), sd 12, n=60/group. Teaching point: a visible gap is not automatically a real one; shrink n and the test can stop being significant.\n\nCurriculum (NZ): NZC S7-1 / S8-1 (enquiry cycle, inference); NCEA AS91264 (L2 inference), AS91582 (L3 formal inference).\nNCEA is transitional: L1 removed from 2028; NZCE (Yr12) 2029; NZACE (Yr13) 2030. Standards below remain valid through the change.\n\nFull mapping + worked walkthrough: classroom-handbook.html",
